data.value:
*To add a new asset, click Input Button. Fill the necessary information. All informations must be defined with exceptions to Asset ID and Asset Purchase Details. You will see a message indicating that your asset has been saved in the database. Otherwise, you will not be redirected and the details left out shall be marked red.
*To search for an asset, click Seach Button. Key in the Asset ID for a particular asset. Note that the Asset ID is the Category Tag and an associated number. Possible results for all searches with an incomplete Asset ID shall also be retrieved. (e.g. input of L instead of LI5).
*To find assets logged on a specific time range, assets of a particular category or assets of the same name, click History Button. The results of any of the three searches may be is made into a report as .csv file.
*To calculate Depreciation of assets of a certain category, click Depreciation Button. With a chosen category, the system shall calculate its Monthly Depreciation, Accumulated Depreciation and Book Value depending on indicated dates.
